#Text=Tornado hits downtown Atlanta
#Text=Saturday , March 15 , 2008
#Text=A tornado , spawned from a large storm , has hit the United States city of Atlanta , Georgia , causing extensive damage throughout the city .
#Text=The National Weather Service confirmed Saturday morning that it was a tornado that struck the city .
#Text=After reviewing the aftermath of the storm , they classified it as an EF2 tornado on the Enhanced Fujita scale .
#Text=Atlanta mayor Shirley Franklin says she is beginning to apply for federal disaster aid .
#Text=There have been no confirmed deaths , but the mayor 's spokeswoman says there may be dead victims trapped within the ruins of a collapsed loft complex .
#Text=The Fulton Cotton Mill Lofts are located in the historic Cabbagetown neighborhood , where at least 20 homes were destroyed .
#Text=" It looks like a bomb went off , it looks like World War III , " said Mahsud Olufani , who has an art studio in the neighbourhood .
#Text=" It 's a disaster area . "
#Text=At least 27 people suffered injuries , mostly cuts and bruises .
#Text=One person is reported to be in critical condition .
#Text=Grady Memorial Hospital , where many of the injured were taken , had suffered some window damage but was still operating .
#Text=Around 50 people have been taken to a local Red Cross shelter for displaced residents .
#Text=The tornado struck during the semifinal game of the SEC Basktetball Tournament between Mississippi State and Alabama .
#Text=Play was stopped with around 2 minutes to go in overtime when heavy wind could be heard outside with rippling of the roof .
#Text=Damage was done to the roof as debris fell to the floor .
#Text=No injuries were reported in the Dome .
#Text=" I thought it was a tornado or a terrorist attack , " said Mississippi State guard Ben Hansbrough .
#Text=The storm arrived with little forewarning .
#Text=A tornado warning was issued for the downtown area a few minutes before the storm hit . "

#Text=Ironically , the guy behind me got a phone call saying there was a tornado warning ,  said Lisa Lynn , who was attending the game at the Georgia Dome . "

column1: #Text=And in two seconds , we heard the noise and things started to shake .
#Text=It was creepy . "

#Text=Another large storm , currently in Mississippi , is heading towards Atlanta , and is forecast to arrive around 3 p.m. National Weather Service meteorologist Mike Leary said Friday 's storm could be  nothing to compare with what 's coming in tomorrow " .

column1: #Text=All downtown events scheduled to occur Saturday have been cancelled .
#Text=This includes the city 's Saint Patrick 's Day parade .
#Text=The remaining SEC tournament games are to be played at Georgia Tech 's Alexander Memorial Coliseum , located in the undamaged midtown .
